<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1264.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram January 27. I do not know the nature of French Minister’s
                            new instructions except by inference. The fact that the Minister had
                            previously given us a paraphrase of his instructions requiring six
                            general advisers, and has now authorized his banker to sign a letter
                            promising advance with advisers limited to service of loan, tended to
                            confirm report that his former instructions were revoked. He has not
                            since conferred with his colleagues.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>